n* Italian: {{t+|it|andare}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|向かう|tr=[[むかう]], mukau}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t-check|kmr|berê xwe dan derekê}}, {{t-check|kmr|ber bi derekê ve çûn}} <!-- link as t-SOP if non-idiomatic -->\n* Malay: {{t|ms|menuju}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|ahu}}, {{t|mi|naka}}, {{t|mi|neke}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|kierować się}}, {{t|pl|brać azymut|impf}}, {{t|pl|wziąć azymut|pf}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|[[dirigir]]-[[se]]}}, {{t|pt|[[encaminhar]]-[[se]]}}, {{t+|pt|rumar}}, {{t+|pt|ir}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|направля́ться|impf}}, {{t+|ru|напра́виться|pf}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|ísť}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|dirigirse}}, {{t+|es|ir}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|åka}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|прямува́ти|impf}}, {{t|uk|попрямува́ти|pf}}, {{t|uk|направля́тися|impf}}, {{t|uk|напра́витися|pf}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|fishing: to remove the head from a fish}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|обезглавявам|impf}}, {{t|bg|обезглавя|pf}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|senkapigi}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[poistaa]] [[pää]]}}\n* German: {{t+|de|köpfen}}, {{t|de|[[den]] [[Kopf]] [[entfernen]]}}\n* Icelandic: {{t|is|hausa}}, {{t|is|afhausa}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to originate, as a river}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|извирам}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|fonti}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|saada alkunsa}}\n* German: {{t+|de|entspringen}}, {{t|de|[[seinen]] [[Ursprung]] [[nehmen]]}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|ered}}, {{t+|hu|fakad}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to form a head}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t|cmn|結球|tr=jiēqiú}} {{qualifier|for crucifiers}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kapumi}}, {{t|eo|kapi}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[muodostaa]] [[kaalinpää]]}}\n* German: {{t|de|[[einen]] [[Kopf]] [[bilden]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to fit or furnish with a head}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kapizi}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[tehdä]] [[pää]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to cut off the top of}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|senkapigi}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|katkaista}}\n* German: {{t+|de|köpfen}}, {{t|de|[[die]] [[Spitze]] [[abschneiden]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|to behead|behead}}\n\n{{trans-top|to go in front of}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|antaŭi}}\n* German: {{t+|de|vorausgehen}}, {{t|de|[[vor]] ([[einem]]/[[etwas]]) [[gehen]]}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|encabeçar}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to get in the front of, so as to hinder or stop}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|alfronti}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|pysäyttää}}\n* German: {{t+|de|entgegenkommen}}, {{t|de|in die Quere kommen}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to set on the head}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|[[поставям]] [[на]] [[глава]]|impf}}, {{t|bg|[[поставя]] [[на]] [[глава]]}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[nostaa]] [[pystyyn]]}}\n* German: {{t|de|[[auf]] [[den]] [[Kopf]] [[setzen]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Esperanto: {{t-check|eo|direktiĝi}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|heed}}, from {{inh|en|ang|hēafod-||main}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*haubida-}}, derived from the noun {{m|gmw-pro|*haubid||head}}. \n\nCognate with {{cog|stq|hööft-}}, {{cog|fy|haad-}}, {{cog|nl|hoofd-}}, {{cog|nds-de|höövd-}}, {{cog|de|haupt-}}.\n\n====Adjective====\n{{en-adj|-}}\n\n# Foremost in rank or importance.\n#: {{syn|en|chief}}\n#: {{ux|en|the '''head''' cook}}\n#* {{RQ:Maxwell Mirror and the Lamp|chapter=XXXIX|page=307|passage=At the far end of the houses the '''head''' gardener stood waiting for his mistress, and he gave her strips of bass to tie up her nosegay. This she did slowly and laboriously, with knuckly old fingers that shook.}}\n# Placed at the top or the front.\n#: {{syn|en|first|top}}\n# Coming from in front.\n#: {{syn|en|foot|tail}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''head''' sea}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''head''' wind}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|foremost in rank or importance}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|челен}}, {{t+|bg|преден}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|cap}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|ĉefa|s}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|pää-}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Haupt|alt=Haupt-}}\n*: Swabian: {{t|swg|Haubd-}}\n* Greek:\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ἀρχι-}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|ראש|tr=rosh}}, {{t+|he|ראשי}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|प्रधान|m}}, {{t+|hi|प्रमुख|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|チーフ|tr=chīfu}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|no|hoved-}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|mor}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|гла́вный}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|hlavný}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|gláven}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|främst}}, {{t+|sv|först}}, {{t-check|sv|compounds with [[huvud]] and [[topp]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|placed at the top or the front}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|преден}}, {{t+|bg|горен}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|antaŭa|s}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|etu-}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|ראש|tr=rosh}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|先頭の|tr=せんとうの, sentō no}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|no|leder-}}, {{t+|no|første}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|пере́дний}}, {{t+|ru|ве́рхний}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|gláven}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|främst}}, {{t+|sv|först}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|coming from in front}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|насрещен}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|vasta-}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|向かい|tr=むかい, mukai-}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|czołowy}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|à cabeça}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|встре́чный}}\n* Swedish: {{t+check|sv|mot|alt=mot-}} {{attention|sv|2=was \"[[mot]]-\" - assumed inflected form or vocalised spelling; please verify if linking is acceptable. see [[User:So9q/Improved-xte.js/documentation#Translation_fixing]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=adeh|DHEA|ahed|hade}}\n\n{{c|en|Body parts|Animal body parts|Cuts of meat|Leaders}}\n\n==Estonian==\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|et|adjective form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|et|hea||par|s|;|nom|p}}"}}